The Brazilian government is
studying tax breaks to manufacturers of notebook and laptop
computers, televisions and cellular phones, Science and
Technology Minister Aloizio Mercadante told reporters in
Brasilia.  The tax breaks would be similar to what has already been
given to tablet makers, Mercadante said.  Apple Inc. (AAPL) â€™s iPads and iPhones will start being produced in
